  <title>Cogl.Framebuffer.prototype.set_stereo_mode</title>
  <synopsis><code mime="text/x-gjs">
function set_stereo_mode(stereo_mode: <link xref="Cogl.StereoMode">Cogl.StereoMode</link>): void {
    // Gjs wrapper for cogl_framebuffer_set_stereo_mode()
}
  </code></synopsis>
  <p>Sets which stereo buffers should be drawn to. The default
is <link xref="Cogl.StereoMode"/>.both, which means that both the left and
right buffers will be affected by drawing. For this to have
an effect, the display system must support stereo drawables,
and the framebuffer must have been created with stereo
enabled. (See <link xref="Cogl.OnscreenTemplate.set_stereo_enabled"/>,
<link xref="Cogl.Framebuffer.get_is_stereo"/>.)</p>
  <p>Since 1.20</p>
<terms>
<item>
<title><code>stereo_mode</code></title>
  <p>A <link xref="Cogl.StereoMode"/> specifying which stereo buffers
              should be drawn tow.</p>
